article.headline: No. 13 Washington women beat cold-shooting Fresno St. 85-54
article.linkText: No. 13 Washington women beat cold-shooting Fresno St. 85-54
article.story:
SEATTLE --  Kelsey Plum scored 30 points, and Chantel Osahor grabbed a career-high 22 rebounds and added 13 points as No. 13 Washington rolled to an 85-54 victory over Fresno State on Sunday for its fifth straight win.

Washington (8-1, 5-0) had a one-point lead with 3:31 remaining the third quarter. The Huskies closed on a 36-6 run, with Plum scoring 11 points and Osahor adding seven during the stretch. Fresno State missed 13 straight field goals before Anais Kirvan made a jump shot with 1:49 left.

Plum, who entered the game as the nation's scoring leader averaging 29.6 points, made 11 of 21 from the field. Plum is 53 points shy of breaking the Pac-12 career scoring record. Osahor, the nation's leading rebounder, had her 20th career double-double.

Natalie Romeo added 18 points and Katie Collier had 10 for the Huskies.

Candice White scored 19 points to lead Fresno State (4-3). Bego Faz Davalos added 11 points and 13 rebounds.
